05/http://www.afro.who.int/en/clusters-a-programmes/dpc/epidemic-a-pandemic-alert-and-response/outbreak-news.html | archivedate=24 April 2015 | df=dmy-all }}{{Fastdelta}}</ref> All numbers are correlated with [[UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs]] (OCHA), if available.<ref group=\"Resource\">{{cite web | url=https://wca.humanitarianresponse.info/en | title=West and Central Africa | website=HumanitarianResponse.info | publisher=[[OCHA]] |accessdate= 11 April 2015}}</ref> The reports were sourced from official information from the affected countries' health ministries. The WHO has stated that the reported numbers \"vastly underestimate the magnitude of the outbreak\", estimating there may be three times as many cases as officially reported.<ref name=\"CDC Estimating future number of cases\" /><ref name=\"Reuters\">{{cite news | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/22/us-health-ebola-who-idUSKCN0IB23220141022 | title=Official WHO Ebola toll near 5,000 with true number nearer 15,000 | work=[[Reuters]] | date=22 October 2014  |accessdate= 11 April 2015| author=Miles, Tom }}</ref><ref name=\"WHO 2014-08-22\">{{cite web|url=http://www.afro.who.int/en/clusters-a-programmes/dpc/epidemic-a-pandemic-alert-and-response/outbreak-news/4260-ebola-virus-disease-west-africa-22-august-2014.html|title=Ebola virus disease, West Africa|date=22 August 2014|publisher=WHO|accessdate=18 September 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140920193115/http://www.afro.who.int/en/clusters-a-programmes/dpc/epidemic-a-pandemic-alert-and-response/outbreak-news/4260-ebola-virus-disease-west-africa-22-august-2014.html|archivedate=20 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><br>Note 3: Date is the \"as of\" date from the reference. A single source may report statistics for multiple \"as of\" dates.\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; white-space:nowrap; width:100%;\"\n|+Minor Ebola virus outbreaks by country and by date \u2013 30 July 2014 t