ategory:Politicians awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for Hazel Grove]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly life and career:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1981-5 \u2192 1981\u20135", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Stunell"}
{"title_page": "Pierino Baffi", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Pierino Baffi\n| image       =Pierino Baffi 1958.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| caption = Baffi in 1958\n| fullname    = Pierino Baffi\n| nickname    =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date|df=yes|1930|9|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Vailate]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|df=yes|1985|03|27|1930|9|15}}\n| death_place =\n| discipline  = Road\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = Sprinter\n| proyears1   = 1954&ndash;1956\n| proteam1    = Nivea-Fuchs\n| proyears2   = 1957\n| proteam2    = Arbos-Bif Welter\n| proyears3   = 1958\n| proteam3    = Chlorodont-Leo\n| proyears4   = 1959\n| proteam4    = Ignis-Frejus\n| proyears5   = 1960\n| proteam5    = Ignis\n| proyears6   = 1961\n| proteam6    = Fides\n| proyears7   = 1962\n| proteam7    = Ghigi\n| proyears8   = 1963&ndash;1964\n| proteam8    = Molteni\n| proyears9   = 1965\n| proteam9    = Bianchi-Mobylette\n| proyears10  = 1966\n| proteam10   = G.B.C.\n| majorwins   = Giro d'Italia, 4 stages<br>Tour de France, 5 stages<br>Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a, 4 stages\n}}\n'''Pierino Baffi''' (15 September 1930 \u2013 27 March 1985) was an [[Italian people|Italian]] professional [[road bicycle racer]]. In 1958 he won stages in all three of the [[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]], becoming the second cyclist (after [[Miguel Poblet]]) to win stages in all three of the Grand Tours in the same year. As of 2016, this has only been repeated by [[Alessandro Petacchi]] in 2003. Baffi's son [[Adriano Baffi|Adriano]] also became a professional cyclist.<ref>{{cycling archives|501}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1955\n:1st, Stages 6 & 9, [[1955 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n;1956\n:1st, [[Giro di Romagna]]\n:1st, [[Milano\u2013Vignola]]\n:1st, Stage 10, [[1956 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1957\n:1st, Stages 8 & 19, [[1957 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n;1958\n:1st, Stage 12, [[1958 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:1st, Stages 10, 16 & 24, [[1958 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n:1st, Stages 3 & 14, [[1958 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n;1959\n:1st, [[Milano-Mantua]]\n:1st, Stage 9, [[Paris\u2013Nice]]\n:1st, Stage 7b, [[Roma-Naples-Roma]]\n;1960\n:1st, [[Giro dell'Emilia]]\n:1st, [[Trofeo Fenaroli]]\n:1st, Stage 6, [[1960 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:1st, Stage 4a, [[Roma-Naples-Roma]]\n;1962\n:1st, [[Coppa Bernocchi]]\n:1st, [[Milano-Mantua]]\n:1st, [[Trofeo Matteotti]]\n;1963\n:1st, [[Trofeo Matteotti]]\n:1st, Stage 2, [[1963 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:1st, Stage 1 & 4, [[Tour de Luxembourg]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Pierino Baffi}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Baffi, Pierino}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:1985 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Cremona]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Italian Giro d'Italia stage winners]]\n[[Category:Italian Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:Italian Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lombardy]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-1930s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Pierino Baffi\n| image       =Pierino Baffi 1958.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| caption = Baffi in 1958\n| fullname    = Pierino Baffi\n| nickname    =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date|df=yes|1930|9|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Vailate]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|df=yes|1985|03|27|1930|9|15}}\n| death_place =\n| discipline  = Road\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = Sprinter\n| proyears1   = 1954&ndash;1956\n| proteam1    = Nivea-Fuchs\n| proyears2   = 1957\n| proteam2    = Arbos-Bif Welter\n| proyears3   = 1958\n| proteam3    = Chlorodont-Leo\n| proyears4   = 1959\n| proteam4    = Ignis-Frejus\n| proyears5   = 1960\n| proteam5    = Ignis\n| proyears6   = 1961\n| proteam6    = Fides\n| proyears7   = 1962\n| proteam7    = Ghigi\n| proyears8   = 1963&ndash;1964\n| proteam8    = Molteni\n| proyears9   = 1965\n| proteam9    = Bianchi-Mobylette\n| proyears10  = 1966\n| proteam10   = G.B.C.\n| majorwins   = Giro d'Italia, 4 stages<br>Tour de France, 5 stages<br>Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a, 4 stages\n}}\n'''Pierino Baffi''' (15 September 1930 \u2013 27 March 1985) was an [[Italian people|Italian]] professional [[road bicycle racer]]. In 1958 he won stages in all three of the [[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]], becoming the second cyclist (after [[Miguel Poblet]]) to win stages in all three of the Grand Tours in the same year. As of 2016, this has only been repeated by [[Alessandro Petacchi]] in 2003. Baffi's son [[Adriano Baffi|Adriano]] also became a professional cyclist.<ref>{{cycling archives|501}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1955\n:1st, Stages 6 & 9, [[1955 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n;1956\n:1st, [[Giro di Romagna]]\n:1st, [[Milano\u2013Vignola]]\n:1st, Stage 10, [[1956 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1957\n:1st, Stages 8 & 19, [[1957 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n;1958\n:1st, Stage 12, [[1958 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:1st, Stages 10, 16 & 24, [[1958 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n:1st, Stages 3 & 14, [[1958 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n;1959\n:1st, [[Milano-Mantua]]\n:1st, Stage 9, [[Paris\u2013Nice]]\n:1st, Stage 7b, [[Roma-Naples-Roma]]\n;1960\n:1st, [[Giro dell'Emilia]]\n:1st, [[Trofeo Fenaroli]]\n:1st, Stage 6, [[1960 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:1st, Stage 4a, [[Roma-Naples-Roma]]\n;1962\n:1st, [[Coppa Bernocchi]]\n:1st, [[Milano-Mantua]]\n:1st, [[Trofeo Matteotti]]\n;1963\n:1st, [[Trofeo Matteotti]]\n:1st, Stage 2, [[1963 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:1st, Stage 1 & 4, [[Tour de Luxembourg]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Pierino Baffi}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{